Package: alocv
Title: Approximate Leave-one-out Computation
Version: 0.0.0.9100
Authors@R: c(person("Wenda", "Zhou", email = "wz2335@columbia.edu", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Peng", "Xu", email = "px2132@columbia.edu", role = "aut"),
    person("Linyun", "He", email = "lh2870@columbia.edu", role = "ctb"))
Description: Efficient methods to estimate out of sample risk for penalized generalized linear
    smoothers. Currently supports lasso / elastic-net GLMs and classification SVMs. The formulas
    are based on leave-one-out approximations as described in the paper linked in the URL below.
URL: https://arxiv.org/abs/1810.02716, https://github.com/wendazhou/alocv-package
Depends: R (>= 3.4)
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
LinkingTo: Rcpp
Imports:
    Rcpp
Suggests:
    glmnet,
    e1071,
    testthat,
    withr,
    knitr,
    rmarkdown
RoxygenNote: 7.1.1
VignetteBuilder: knitr
